etymologies: Middle English: from Anglo-Latin stracus, straca; probably from the Germanic base of the verb stretch

definitions: a continuous line of planking or plates from the stem to the stern of a ship or boat.
shortDefinitions: continuous line of planking or plates from stem to stern of ship or boat

definitions: a protruding ridge fitted to an aircraft or other structure to improve aerodynamic stability.
shortDefinitions: protruding ridge fitted to aircraft or other structure
